    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wedge-shaped boards placed at the lower edges of sloping roofs to raise slightly the lowest course of tiles or slate in order to give that course the same pitch as the courses above.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
